The paper deals with the construction and analysis of codes for list decoding from insertions and deletions, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of the feasibility region for such codes, which can be seen as a problem in discrete structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of concatenation schemes for constructing efficient codes, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.SI) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
